name: Air Terjun. Twin waterfall Lipah Petang
address: J6C5+CX4, Jl. Lipah, Petang, Kec. Petang, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80353, Indonesia
review 1: I was the only one there. Not easy to find, path was grown over and very slippery. At the waterfall the fence was broken by rocks and trees that must have fallen of the cliff wall just few days prior during the storm, quite scary.
review 2: Still new spot for waterfals seekers and also not so crowded. The public facilities also well maintained. The access to the waterfal also good and not so far from the ticket counter. We really have a great time here. Better you come in the morning time.
review 3: I went there and no one was there, the way down was quiet far, you have to be careful.  because it's a little slippery maybe because it's raining and the water isn't clear but the waterfall is nice and if you come here don't forget to bring drinking water because there are no warung
